Low/Medium: day 2 of personal narratives unit (need to print student copies of page 22 of document). Students choose a small moment to write about and brainstorm ideas. First have students share with a partner orally about their event using transition words (First, then, next, after that, finally…) before writing or drawing details.

High:

Teacher will model the process of writing a personal narrative for the whole group. I would suggest writing about something you all have in common. First day of school, the School Day yesterday, or a field trip from last year.
Focus on what to do if you get to a word that’s hard to spell by clapping syllables. Focus on Capital letters and full stops. Focus on getting one complete sentence for each section. Then allow time for the students to work on the same. Once or if time allows, then move to adding 3 sentences per section from First-Finally.', '[]'::jsonb, '', '[]'::jsonb, '{}'::uuid[], 2)
