Low/Medium: day 3 of personal narratives unit. Need to print student copies of page 25 of document. Students draw out their narrative - beginning, middle, and end. First have students share with a partner orally about their event using transition words (First, then, next, after that, finally…) before drawing. Encourage them to get their ideas on paper - tomorrow we will add more details.

High:

Students should have been practicing orally what to say already.
 They should also know from your whole group example.

Students take A3 paper and fold it into eights. Write the following in each rectangle:
title, orientation, first, then, next after that, finally, I felt.

This is the structure for the Personal Narrative. For the orientation, please help students create the sentence. help them by asking when, who, and what. (example: Last Thursday, my family and I went to the cinema.)

Each section of the draft paper should now have only 1 sentence. (Example: First we got into the car.) Continue to tell what happened in each section using only 1 sentence.', '[]'::jsonb, '', '[]'::jsonb, '{}'::uuid[], 2)
