5A- Ufli Lessons

Guided Reading:
Begin long A /a/. Mini lesson on the different spellings (a_e, ai, ay). Discuss with students where you are likely to use each spelling (ai if in the middle of a word, ay if at the end of a word). Have students practice with whiteboards.

Create a class Anchor Chart:

LONG A

baby, tape, snail, tray

Seesaw-ai vs ay practice with sentences
SeeSaw-Long A
SeeSaw-Long A Word Build with silent e
SeeSaw- Long A Word Build
SeeSaw-Word Sort with Long A

KG IXL- Find Long A
G2-Spell the long A words

Review Syllabication-  Be sure to explain that usually every syllable in the English language has at least 1 vowel.
***Try to avoid clapping. Show them how to use their mouths instead. Often the clapping can lead to errors. Therefore, students should count every time their mouth drops/opens as a syllable. Practice some words. List of Multisyllabic words.

SeeSaw Activities: (Syllables)
Counting syllables SeeSaw
Syllables picture sort

Rotations:
long a center activities and independent work
Long vs. short vowel sort
Long a activities (inc. bingo)
A_e Seesaw
A_e Seesaw
ai/ay word sort SeeSaw
ai/ay write the word (word bank included) SeeSaw
a_e/ai/ay word sort and read SeeSaw
Decodable text hub

Previous Week Rotation:
No prep phonics:
Number word packet
Color word packet
Roll and Write My Words
Sight Word Searches
Syllables with pictures
Syllables without pictures (Split the line)
Syllables with pictures
Syllables without pictures (Split the line)
Syllable Sort
Syllable Sort (Pink)
G3- IXL EASY Read Multi-Syllable Words

Short Vowel Review-short vowel reader’s theater
Decodable te', '["Students will become familiar with the classroom environment."]'::jsonb, 'Assessment: RAZ Reading, phonemic awareness and phonics assessment

Nouns-Kahoot

Differentiation: Lower: SeeSaw, Syllables, Syllables 2,
Higher: SeeSaw', '[]'::jsonb, '{}'::uuid[], 1)
