insert into master_core_lesson_events
  (id, unit_id, subject_id, week_number, day_of_week, title, directions, learning_objectives, notes, resources, standards, display_order_within_day)
  values ('3948ae68-6a29-5a8a-88a9-bd3f48dd138f', 'a3af9977-9ab6-5857-9cb0-68a3faab31db', '00000000-0000-0000-0000-0000000005d7', 8, 'wed'::weekday, 'Writing up Experiments/Investigations', 'Writing up Experiments/Investigations

An experiment (fair test) is a procedure carried out to test a hypothesis, usually involving controlled and uncontrolled environments, while an investigation is an examination or inquiry that aims to uncover facts about a broad topic.

Tell the students that they are going to write up what they did yesterday using the template they will be using for the Science Fair - in padlet:
Write up for Science Fair
From slide 5 - the hypothesis

The hypothesis is an educated guess as to what will happen during your experiment. The hypothesis is often written using the words "IF" and "THEN."

A hypothesis for adding baking soda to lemon juice, vinegar, and water with a focus on the chemical reactions that occur due to the acidity of the liquids:
Hypothesis: If baking soda is added to lemon juice, vinegar, and water, then the lemon juice and vinegar will not act the same compared to water, because they are acidic and will react with the baking soda (a base), while water will not do anything (being neutral, will show little or no reaction).
They can also attempt recording the outcome in a graph.

(generated by Chat GPT - with slight modifications)

Inserted in padlet', '[]'::jsonb, 'Note: Day 1 & 2 can be combined - doing as much as can be done. Day 4 & 5 can be combined or as much as can be done taken from these 2 sessions Please make use of the cooking sessions during writing to cover some of the concepts being looked at here.

Std: 5-PS1-2: Measure and graph quantities to provide evidence that regardless of the type of change that occurs when heating, cooling, or mixing substances, the total weight of matter is conserved.

Assessment: What things happen that lets us know a material is a good insulator

Differentiation: Can say what makes a material  an insulator
Can name 2 materials that are insulators with some support
Can name more than 2 insulators independently.', '[]'::jsonb, '{}'::uuid[], 6)
