insert into master_core_lesson_events
  (id, unit_id, subject_id, week_number, day_of_week, title, directions, learning_objectives, notes, resources, standards, display_order_within_day)
  values ('4ec8dc4a-1f5d-5837-b5eb-eda6967cde04', '2209bbbb-6204-5e62-bbe5-2ef3fa2f036b', '00000000-0000-0000-0000-0000000005d2', 10, 'mon'::weekday, 'Guided Reading', 'Guided Reading:

Warm-Up:
Review first-person point of view. Ask a few students to give an example of a first-person sentence.

Mini-Lesson (5 minutes)
Read a short passage from a first-person narrator (e.g., a short excerpt from a children’s book like Diary of a Wimpy Kid or The One and Only Ivan or any book from the mentor text list below) .
Discuss how the story feels more personal because we are inside the character’s head.
Activity (5 minutes)
Have students write a 3-4 sentence story from the first-person perspective. Start with a prompt like: "I was walking through the park when..."
After writing, students can share their stories with a partner.
Wrap-up (2 minutes)
Ask students: "How does it feel to write from your character''s perspective? How do you know it''s first person?"

Rotations:
See list from Sunday or the differentiation section below.', '[]'::jsonb, 'Std: 📘 Reading Literature (RL)
CCSS.ELA-LITERACY.RL.5.4 Determine the meaning of words and phrases as they are used in a text, including figurative language such as metaphors and similes.
EE.RL.5.4 Determine the meaning of words and phrases in a text.
📝 Language (L)
CCSS.ELA-LITERACY.L.5.2.AUse punctuation to separate items in a series.
EE.L.5.2.A Use ending punctuation when writing a sentence.
CCSS.ELA-LITERACY.L.5.1.CUse verb tense to convey various times, sequences, states, and conditions.
EE.L.5.1.GUse appropriate verb forms to convey present and past tense.
🔤 Reading Foundational Skills (RF)
CCSS.ELA-LITERACY.RF.5.3.C Use context to confirm or self-correct word recognition and understanding, rereading as necessary.
EE.RF.5.3.CUse context to confirm word recognition and understanding.
CCSS.ELA-LITERACY.RF.5.3Know and apply grade-level phonics and word analysis skills in decoding words.
EE.RF.5.3Use letter-sound knowledge and syllabication patterns to read words.
✍️ Writing (W)
CCSS.ELA-LITERACY.W.5.2.BDevelop the topic with facts, definitions, concrete details, quotations, or other information and examples related to the topic.
CCSS.ELA-LITERACY.W.5.3.CUse a variety of transitional words, phrases, and clauses to manage the sequence of events.
CSS.ELA-LITERACY.W.5.4Produce clear and coherent writing in which the development and organization are appropriate to task, purpose, and audience.

Assessment: Informal Observations

Differentiation: Use these mentor text to talk about transitional words (link in pic):', '[]'::jsonb, '{}'::uuid[], 1)
