insert into master_core_lesson_events
  (id, unit_id, subject_id, week_number, day_of_week, title, directions, learning_objectives, notes, resources, standards, display_order_within_day)
  values ('1067a47c-98ec-5c3f-b381-37f3b9bf42bd', 'a3af9977-9ab6-5857-9cb0-68a3faab31db', '00000000-0000-0000-0000-0000000005d7', 10, 'mon'::weekday, 'Students continue with the investigation for this week linked to Electrical…', 'Students continue with the investigation for this week linked to Electrical Conductors - this is to build upon what students found out from the Thermal Conductor investigation & knowledge gained from looking at circuits from the previous day.

Students start off with putting in batteries for a torch to work - one torch between 2. This to be followed by investigating and completing electric circuits on rotation. (see image below)
What happens when an electric current flows through a conductor?
When current passes through a conductor, like a wire, all of the electrons which were flowing randomly in various directions, all get together and begin to move in the same direction. Electrons flow from the negative - through the conductor to the positive +. They are repelled by the negative terminal and attracted by the positive terminal.
Conductors – a conductor is a material that has electrons moving freely. This means that, when electricity is passed through, the electrons move, and the electricity passes through the material.
Insulators – an electrical insulator is a material that does not have electrons flowing freely, making it almost impossible to conduct electricity.

Sheet to be completed for circuit 5 to finish off the session.
Whole class can check their prediction on what happens when there are 2 bulbs in a circuit.', '[]'::jsonb, 'Std: 3.02d Be able to explain and justify their predictions, investigations, findings, and conclusions

Assessment: What will happen if..?

Differentiation: Can name parts of a simple circuit
Can talk about what is happening when the circuit is connected
Can talk about, predict,  and explain what is happening when the circuit is connected - making predictions about what would happen when changes are made to the circuit e.g adding another battery', '[]'::jsonb, '{}'::uuid[], 6)
