  values ('a34ce428-28d4-5c19-af4e-5b7db9bc04e3', 'c6063524-6b87-5315-8c24-a77c123ca5b3', '00000000-0000-0000-0000-0000000005d1', 11, 'sun'::weekday, 'Day 1: Numerical Patterns / Input & Output Tables', 'Day 1: Numerical Patterns / Input & Output Tables', '["Students will be able to identify, describe, and extend numerical patterns. They will use input-output tables to find and apply a rule (e.g., add 3, multiply by 2) that connects a set of inputs to a set of outputs.", "Description: This lesson focuses on algebraic reasoning through patterns. Students will analyze sequences of numbers and values in \"In-Out\" tables to determine the operation (add, subtract, multiply, or divide) that defines the pattern''s rule. They will then use this rule to find missing values.", "CCSS: CCSS.MATH.CONTENT.5.OA.B.3: Generate two numerical patterns using two given rules. Identify apparent relationships between corresponding terms. Form ordered pairs consisting of corresponding terms from the two patterns, and graph the ordered pairs on a coordinate plane."]'::jsonb, 'Differentiation: Each lesson includes partner practice, common misperceptions independent practice, and a challenge questions for differentiation.', '[]'::jsonb, '{}'::uuid[], 0)
