  values ('c8357868-201f-5720-872b-30a5a6187d6b', '26d7d07b-c350-518f-ab6d-c9775b3a00dd', '00000000-0000-0000-0000-0000000005d4', 11, 'mon'::weekday, 'Grammar', 'Grammar:
Warm-Up (3 minutes)
Review Day 1’s pronouns by having students call out pronouns they remember from the anchor chart.

Main Activity (10 minutes)
Explain subject pronouns (used as the subject of a sentence) and object pronouns (used after an action verb or preposition).
Give students a handout with simple sentences, where they circle subject pronouns and underline object pronouns.

Wrap-Up (2 minutes)
Call on a few students to share examples of subject and object pronouns from the handout.
Review with the class by asking, "What’s the difference between subject and object pronouns?" Update the anchor chart with their answers.', '[]'::jsonb, '', '[]'::jsonb, '{}'::uuid[], 3)
