  values ('74f5c7d3-b37d-588a-a08e-ffb5caa417d5', '2209bbbb-6204-5e62-bbe5-2ef3fa2f036b', '00000000-0000-0000-0000-0000000005d2', 11, 'wed'::weekday, 'Guided Reading', 'Guided Reading:

Introduction (3 mins):Define idioms as expressions that don’t mean exactly what the words say (e.g., “It’s raining cats and dogs”).
Video (3 mins):Show the idioms video and ask students to listen for examples.
Video with When Pigs Fly
Practice (4 mins):Review examples and ask students to come up with sentences using idioms from a worksheet.

Rotations:
See list from Sunday or the differentiation section below.', '[]'::jsonb, 'Std: Reading:
RL.5.2Determine a theme of a story, drama, or poem from details in the text, including how characters in a story or drama respond to challenges or how the speaker in a poem reflects upon a topic; summarize the text.
EE.RL.5.2(Essential Element) Often a simplified version of RL.5.2, such as summarize a portion of text (e.g., a paragraph or chapter) or determine the theme of a story/drama.
RL.5.9Compare and contrast stories in the same genre (e.g., mysteries and adventure stories) on their approaches to similar themes and topics.
EE.RL.5.9(Essential Element) Often a simplified version of RL.5.9, such as compare and contrast texts in the same genre or with similar topics/themes.
Grammar:
L.5.1.F Use verb tense to convey various times, sequences, states, and conditions
.EE.L.5.1.H(Essential Element) Often a simplified version of L.5.1, focusing on using grade-appropriate conventions of standard English grammar when writing or speaking.
Writing:
W.5.5With guidance and support from peers and adults, develop and strengthen writing as needed by planning, revising, editing, rewriting, or trying a new approach.

Assessment: Informal Assessment: Seesaw/IXL

Differentiation: IXL and Seesaw can be differentiated by student to student or class to class.', '[]'::jsonb, '{}'::uuid[], 1)
