First, review any previous week''s lessons on volume including understanding volume, volume of rectangular prisms, and using volume formula.
Second, Complete project: Design a City with Volume, Area, and Perimeter
 Project Steps
Review concepts using IXL
Review directions and rubric
Cut grid paper, buildings, and roads
Construct 3D buildings and city layout
Calculate volume, area, and perimeter
Decorate with details (cars, trees, etc.)
Record measurements in table
Assemble on construction paper', '["Central Learning Outcome", "Students will apply their understanding of volume, area, and perimeter to design a functional city layout while meeting specific size requirements and rules.", "Supporting Learning Outcomes", "Students will demonstrate mastery of volume calculations for rectangular prisms.", "Students will apply area and perimeter concepts to create a functional city layout.", "Students will develop spatial reasoning and problem-solving skills through hands-on design.", "Students will practice following directions and meeting specific criteria for accuracy and creativity.", "Common Core Standards", "5.MD.C.3: Understand volume as an attribute of solid figures.", "5.MD.C.5: Relate volume to multiplication and addition.", "4.MD.A.3: Apply area and perimeter formulas for rectangles."]'::jsonb, 'Differentiation: Each lesson includes opportunities for partner practice, common misperceptions, independent practice, and a challenge questions for differentiation.

