Warm-up (5 min) – Think-Pair-Share
BrainPOP video on Making Inferences
Share a picture card (See Resource Folder)
Ask: "What do you think will happen next?"
Students pair up and share their predictions.
The Inference Collection - Once Upon a Picture
Practice (7 min) – Inferring from Pictures
Display a picture with a hidden meaning (Example: A boy with a backpack and umbrella looking at the sky).
Ask:
What do you see?
What do you already know about this?
What can you infer?
Use a sentence stem: "I infer that ___ because ___."
Closing (3 min) – Exit Ticket
Students write one inference they made from the picture on a sticky note.
Rotations:
SeeSaw
Pronoun
Pronoun Practice
Pronoun Practice 1
Circle the Pronoun

 IXL
G2 Pronouns
G5 Pronouns
