  values ('f3fe2b02-f4a4-54c9-baf5-af22fad169a8', '3170e847-5264-53cf-bbc6-034ff65e7f0c', '00000000-0000-0000-0000-0000000005d2', 20, 'wed'::weekday, 'Guided Reading', 'Guided Reading:
Warm-up (5 min) – Quick Inferencing Game
Display a sentence with missing information, e.g.,
"Sam was shivering, even though the sun was shining."
Ask: What can we infer?
Practice (7 min) – Writing with Clues
Students write a short mystery scene (3–5 sentences).
The scene should include clues that help readers make inferences.
Pair up and exchange papers. Partners read & infer.
Closing (3 min) – Share & Celebrate
A few students share their mystery sentences with the class.
Class makes inferences & predictions about them.', '[]'::jsonb, 'Std: RL5.1 – Quote accurately from a text when explaining what the text says explicitly and when drawing inferences.
RI5.1 – Quote accurately from a text when explaining what the text says explicitly and when drawing inferences.
EE.RL5.1 – Identify explicit details and make logical inferences from a literary text.
EE.RI5.1 – Identify explicit details and make logical inferences from an informational text.
CC: L.5.1.C – Use verb tense to convey various times, sequences, states, and conditions.
EE.L.5.1.K – Use correct verb tense in sentences.
RI5.8 – Explain how an author uses reasons and evidence to support particular points in a text.
W5.1 – Write opinion pieces supporting a point of view with reasons and information.
W5.2a – Introduce a topic clearly, group related information logically, and include formatting, illustrations, or multimedia when useful.
EE.RI5.2 – Identify the main idea of an informational text and recount key details.

Assessment: Reading- Teacher reads students’ mystery sentences
Listen to peer discussions

Grammar-
Share 1-2 short stories aloud and have classmates identify the pronouns.
Exit Ticket: "Write a sentence using ‘they’ correctly."

Differentiation: Reading- Provide sentence stems
Allow drawing clues for struggling writers

Grammar-
Support: Provide sentence starters for students who need help.
Challenge: Have advanced students write an 8-sentence story with different pronouns.', '[]'::jsonb, '{}'::uuid[], 1)
