Fact and Opinion (2/28)', '[]'::jsonb, 'Std: RI.5.8 – Explain how an author uses reasons and evidence to support particular points in a text.
EE.RI.5.8 – Identify the reasons an author gives to support points in a text.
L.5.3.A – Expand, combine, and reduce sentences for meaning, reader interest, and style.
EE.L.5.3.A – Use language to achieve meaning and clarity when writing or speaking.
RI.5.9 – Integrate information from several texts on the same topic in order to write or speak about the subject knowledgeably.
W.5.2a – Introduce a topic clearly, provide a general observation and focus, and group related information logically.
W.5.8 – Recall relevant information from experiences or gather relevant information from print and digital sources and summarize or paraphrase information in notes and finished work.
EE.RI.5.2 – Identify the main idea of a text and retell key details.
EE.RI.5.3 – Compare two or more individuals, events, or ideas in a text based on specific information.

Assessment: Reading- Exit Ticket: “One fact and one opinion about your favorite animal.”
Collect responses to check understanding.

Grammar- Quick exit ticket: Give a sentence (The ball was kicked by Maria.) and ask students to rewrite it in active voice.

Writing:  Peer or Self-Assessment

Differentiation: Reading-
Struggling learners: Provide sentence starters (e.g., "A fact about school is…").
Advanced learners: Challenge them to find two facts and two opinions in a short text.

Grammar- Struggling students: Provide highlighted sentence structure cues.
Advanced students: Ask them to create their own examples.

Writing:
LA: Provide sentence starters for structuring their writing.
Word bank with key vocabulary (e.g., responsibility, helping, needs, wants, fairness).
Allow students to verbally express their opinions before writing them down.
HA: Encourage them to write a longer paragraph or multiple paragraphs.
include examples or personal experiences to strengthen their reasoning.
Can look at how to put in a counter argument: “Some people think we should not help others because… but I believe…”', '[]'::jsonb, '{}'::uuid[], 1)
