Warm-Up (3 min):
Video: Show a short BrainPOP or YouTube video on active vs. passive voice. (Example: BrainPOP – Active and Passive Voice)
Ask: “What do you notice about how the subject and verb work in the examples?”
Practice (10 min):
Mini-Lesson (5 min)
Write two sentences on the board:
The cat chased the mouse. (Active)
The mouse was chased by the cat. (Passive)
Discuss: Which sentence sounds stronger? Who is doing the action?
Explain the pattern:
Active
Passive
Paired Sorting Activity (5 min)
Provide sentence strips with mixed active/passive sentences.
Pairs sort them into two categories: Active and Passive.', '[]'::jsonb, '', '[]'::jsonb, '{}'::uuid[], 3)
