  values ('f1fea291-7b9b-5a62-ae7d-4e1a397f968e', '93d67480-4087-55ce-befd-2f8da844b357', '00000000-0000-0000-0000-0000000005d7', 21, 'wed'::weekday, 'Key vocabulary', 'Key vocabulary
Map, Sea, Coast, Desert

(5mins)
Show two images:
Desert life (tents, camels)
Coastal life (boats, fishing)
[Teachers to search for images that match ability of class]

Students discuss:
What do you see?
What is different?
Key questions
Is Qatar big or small?
Is it surrounded by land or water?
What do we call land next to the sea?
Coast

(25 mins) Decide which image goes under Desert Life and which goes under Coastal Life.Images can be sorted under the 2 types of living. Hoops can be used with the images placed within the assigned hoops. These images can also be put up on a T-chart or words written instead.

(10 mins) Wrap-up

Students finish:
“One difference between desert life and coastal life  is __________.”', '["To compare desert life and coastal life."]'::jsonb, 'Std: Desert Life or Coastal Life?

Assessment: Listen for vocabulary (boat, tent, fishing, camel)

Differentiation: Teacher-Led: The teacher plays a more active role in guiding discussions and facilitating activities. (generally - as required)

Visual Aids: Use pictures, labels, and visual aids to support understanding.', '[]'::jsonb, '{}'::uuid[], 6)
