Discuss when to use passive voice (e.g., when the doer is unknown or unimportant).
Compare:
The cake was baked last night. (Passive - focus on cake)
Sarah baked the cake last night. (Active - focus on Sarah)
Independent Writing (5 min)
Students write two sentences in active voice and two in passive voice about a topic of their choice.
Peer review: Swap with a partner and check if they used active/passive correctly.', '[]'::jsonb, '', '[]'::jsonb, '{}'::uuid[], 3)
