  values ('26c613e9-412b-54c0-a776-026d92965adf', '3170e847-5264-53cf-bbc6-034ff65e7f0c', '00000000-0000-0000-0000-0000000005d2', 22, 'mon'::weekday, 'Guided Reading', 'Guided Reading:

AND/OR

Warm-Up (3 min):
Play a short YouTube video explaining the SWBST strategy for summarizing.
Quick discussion: What does each letter stand for?
Practice (10 min):
Read a short historical or science passage (Qatar History fun fact, if possible).
Work together to fill in the SWBST chart as a class.
Have students summarize in their own words using this structure.', '[]'::jsonb, 'Std: RI.5.2 – Determine two or more main ideas of a text and explain how they are supported by key details; summarize the text.
EE.RI.5.2 – Identify the main idea of a text and summarize key details.
W.5.1 – Write opinion pieces on topics or texts, supporting a point of view with reasons and information.
W.5.4 – Produce clear and coherent writing in which the development, organization, and style are appropriate to task, purpose, and audience.
W.5.9 – Draw evidence from literary or informational texts to support analysis,

Assessment: Reading- Turn and talk: Share your summary with a partner.
Ask: How does the SWBST strategy help us summarize? Listen to partner discussions.
Check if students use all parts of SWBST correctly.

Grammar-Exit Ticket: Write a sentence with at least one noun and one verb and underline them.
Reflection: Share how nouns and verbs help us understand what the passage is about.

Writing: Review completed "Summarizing Graphic Organizer" for product selection and initial thoughts.

Differentiation: Reading- Struggling learners: Provide a completed example first.
Advanced learners: Have them try summarizing without the SWBST chart.

Grammar- Struggling students: Use a word bank to help identify nouns/verbs.
Advanced students: Write their own short paragraph using at least five nouns and verbs.

Writing:
Use plenty of visuals (pictures, diagrams, real food items) to keep students engaged.', '[]'::jsonb, '{}'::uuid[], 1)
