  values ('8124959d-b1a2-5c1a-9503-1b5c72e0850c', '165cfaae-ffa5-58e5-9d47-eed87e742ea5', '00000000-0000-0000-0000-0000000005d4', 22, 'mon'::weekday, 'Grammar', 'Grammar:

Mentor Text: Alexander and the Terrible, Horrible, No Good, Very Bad Day (or a short nonfiction passage)

BrainPOP video on Nouns & Verbs

Warm-up (10 min)
Game: “Noun or Verb?” – Display words (e.g., run, cat, jump, happiness) and have students stand for nouns, sit for verbs.
Quick review: Watch a short BrainPOP video on nouns and verbs.
Practice (25 min)
Whole Group: Read a short passage (fiction or nonfiction).
Pair Work: Highlight nouns and verbs in the text.
Guided Discussion: What is the main idea of the passage? How do the nouns and verbs help express it?
Independent Practice: Seesaw activity – Sorting nouns and verbs from sentences.', '[]'::jsonb, '', '[]'::jsonb, '{}'::uuid[], 3)
