insert into master_core_lesson_events
  (id, unit_id, subject_id, week_number, day_of_week, title, directions, learning_objectives, notes, resources, standards, display_order_within_day)
  values ('baf886c2-daaf-5742-a317-7f0ade2f119d', '5acb9a7c-064f-5202-bb5d-cd2db57e15fe', '00000000-0000-0000-0000-0000000005d2', 23, 'sun'::weekday, 'Guided Reading', 'Guided Reading:

Warm-Up: (whole group)
The teacher will begin the lesson by briefly reviewing the reading and comprehension skills that were learned in previous classes. This may include identifying characters, setting, plot, and understanding the sequence of events in a story.

Practice:
Reading and comprehension activity: The teacher will provide each group of students with a text that is appropriate for their reading level. This may be a short story, a chapter from a book, a poem, or an informational text. The students will read the text in their groups, discussing the characters, setting, plot, and main ideas. The teacher will circulate around the room, offering support and guidance as needed..  (Can also be done in Guided Reading)

Wrap Up:
The teacher will summarize the main points of the lesson, reinforcing the importance of reading comprehension and summarizing as essential skills for understanding a text. The teacher may review the different strategies for summarizing and how they help identify the main ideas of a text.

Rotations:
SeeSaw
 Dictionary Skills
Guide Words
Practice

 IXL
G3-Dictionary
G4 Dictionary
G5 Dictionary
G3 Dictionary Entry
G4 Dictionary Entry
G5 Dictionary Entry
G5 Thesaurus

Guided Reading Task Card Review', '[]'::jsonb, 'Note: 1. Dates: Rates: (As in, judging or appreciating something; could be used in a poem about appreciating the blessings of dates.) Gates: (Gates of Paradise, gates to the mosque, gates to the house.) States: (As in conditions, describing the different states of fasting or spirituality.) 2. Mosque: Kiosk: (Though not directly Islamic, mosques often have a small kiosk selling religious items.) Disk: (Could be a symbolic reference to knowledge or wisdom gained at the mosque) 3. Prayer: Carer: (Emphasis on the care and devotion put into prayer) Sharer: (Linking prayers to sharing a special time) 4. Star: Far: (Relating to how far the light of guidance can travel, or the distance to Mecca.) 5. Moon: Soon: (Ramadan will be here soon, or the end of fasting day is coming soon.) 6. Iftar: Gifter: (Allah is the ultimate giver, and we are grateful for the Iftar meal.) After: (The time after a long day of fasting.)

Std: L.5.4.C (CCSS)
Consult reference materials (e.g., dictionaries, glossaries, thesauruses), both print and digital, to find the pronunciation and determine or clarify the precise meaning of key words and phrases.
L.5.4 (CCSS)
Determine or clarify the meaning of unknown and multiple-meaning words and phrases based on grade 5 reading and content, choosing flexibly from a range of strategies.
W.5.1.A (CCSS)
Introduce a topic or text clearly, state an opinion, and create an organizational structure in which ideas are logically grouped to support the writer’s purpose.
EE.5.1.1.A (Essential Element)
Introduce a topic or text and state an opinion about it.
W.5.1.B (CCSS)
Provide logically ordered reasons that are supported by facts and details.
EE.5.1.1.B (Essential Element)
Provide at least one reason to support an opinion.
W.5.2.A (CCSS)
Introduce a topic clearly, provide a general observation and focus, and group related information logically; include formatting (e.g., headings), illustrations, and multimedia when useful to aiding

Assessment: Grammar- Quick check-in: "What was easy or hard about using guide words?"
Exit Ticket: “What are two ways a dictionary helps you?” (write on a sticky note).

Writing:
Observe participation in the Rhyme Time Warm-Up and the Rhyme Sort.

Differentiation: Grammar- Support: Provide a simplified dictionary with larger fonts and fewer words per page.
Challenge: Ask advanced students to find multiple definitions and part of speech for a word.

Writing:
Support: Pre-sorted cards, with only a few pairs to sort.
Challenge: Students generate their own rhyming pairs on the topic of Ramadan.', '[]'::jsonb, '{}'::uuid[], 1)
