Session 2: Introducing ABAB Rhyme Scheme
(5 mins) Review:
 Quick review of rhyming. Ask students for examples of rhyming words.
(10 mins) ABAB Explanation:
Introduce the ABAB rhyme scheme using colors or letters to label the rhyming lines. For example:
Line 1: A (red)
Line 2: B (blue)
Line 3: A (red)
Line 4: B (blue)

Rhyme.docx

Use a simple poem as an example and label it together.
(10 mins) ABAB Identification:
Give students several short poems. They identify the rhyme scheme by coloring the corresponding lines in the same color
ABAB Scheme.docx
.
(5 mins) Reflection:
 Ask students to explain in their own words what the ABAB rhyme scheme is.', '[]'::jsonb, '', '[]'::jsonb, '{}'::uuid[], 2)
