Review Previous Lesson', '[]'::jsonb, 'Note: 1. Dates: Rates: (As in, judging or appreciating something; could be used in a poem about appreciating the blessings of dates.) Gates: (Gates of Paradise, gates to the mosque, gates to the house.) States: (As in conditions, describing the different states of fasting or spirituality.) 2. Mosque: Kiosk: (Though not directly Islamic, mosques often have a small kiosk selling religious items.) Disk: (Could be a symbolic reference to knowledge or wisdom gained at the mosque) 3. Prayer: Carer: (Emphasis on the care and devotion put into prayer) Sharer: (Linking prayers to sharing a special time) 4. Star: Far: (Relating to how far the light of guidance can travel, or the distance to Mecca.) 5. Moon: Soon: (Ramadan will be here soon, or the end of fasting day is coming soon.) 6. Iftar: Gifter: (Allah is the ultimate giver, and we are grateful for the Iftar meal.) After: (The time after a long day of fasting.)

Std: L.5.4.C (CCSS)
Consult reference materials (e.g., dictionaries, glossaries, thesauruses), both print and digital, to find the pronunciation and determine or clarify the precise meaning of key words and phrases.
L.5.4 (CCSS)
Determine or clarify the meaning of unknown and multiple-meaning words and phrases based on grade 5 reading and content, choosing flexibly from a range of strategies.
W.5.1.A (CCSS)
Introduce a topic or text clearly, state an opinion, and create an organizational structure in which ideas are logically grouped to support the writer’s purpose.
EE.5.1.1.A (Essential Element)
Introduce a topic or text and state an opinion about it.
W.5.1.B (CCSS)
Provide logically ordered reasons that are supported by facts and details.
EE.5.1.1.B (Essential Element)
Provide at least one reason to support an opinion.
W.5.2.A (CCSS)
Introduce a topic clearly, provide a general observation and focus, and group related information logically; include formatting (e.g., headings), illustrations, and multimedia when useful to aiding

Assessment: Grammar- Reflection: "How can a thesaurus make your writing better?"
Exit Ticket: Write one word and a synonym for it.

Writing:
 Evaluate students'' poems based on correct ABAB rhyme scheme, topic relevance, and effort.

Differentiation: Grammar- Support: Provide a list of words with suggested synonyms to choose from.
Challenge: Have students find antonyms for their words as well.

Writing:

Support: Provide a template with sentence starters and rhyming word suggestions.
Challenge: Encourage students to use more vivid imagery and descriptive language.', '[]'::jsonb, '{}'::uuid[], 1)
