See Sunday’s Options', '[]'::jsonb, 'Note: 1. Dates: Rates: (As in, judging or appreciating something; could be used in a poem about appreciating the blessings of dates.) Gates: (Gates of Paradise, gates to the mosque, gates to the house.) States: (As in conditions, describing the different states of fasting or spirituality.) 2. Mosque: Kiosk: (Though not directly Islamic, mosques often have a small kiosk selling religious items.) Disk: (Could be a symbolic reference to knowledge or wisdom gained at the mosque) 3. Prayer: Carer: (Emphasis on the care and devotion put into prayer) Sharer: (Linking prayers to sharing a special time) 4. Star: Far: (Relating to how far the light of guidance can travel, or the distance to Mecca.) 5. Moon: Soon: (Ramadan will be here soon, or the end of fasting day is coming soon.) 6. Iftar: Gifter: (Allah is the ultimate giver, and we are grateful for the Iftar meal.) After: (The time after a long day of fasting.)

