  values ('a5a6add5-d779-5c15-b2ee-47f14fcc3111', '9ff375f9-74ea-5870-a272-f4e92ccfef7a', '00000000-0000-0000-0000-0000000005d7', 24, 'tue'::weekday, 'Plant Reproduction & Life Cycle', 'Plant Reproduction & Life Cycle
Vocabulary
Life cycle, Seed, Seedling, Adult plant, Reproduction

Ask:
“Which part of the plant helps it reproduce?”
Review: flower

2. Direct Instruction
Show plant life cycle diagram.
Explain stages:
Seed
Seedling
Adult plant
Flower produces seeds
Explain that plants reproduce by making seeds.

3. Video
Show a short life cycle video.
Ask students to watch for:
“What happens after the seed grows?”

4. Guided Activity
Students are shown life cycle cards.
Students make suggestions on which step is next…
“What comes after the seed?”

5. Discussion
Students volunteer to explain the life cycle.

 6. Exit Ticket
Students draw plant cycle:', '[]'::jsonb, 'Std: Know about ways in which plants reproduce.
Gather evidence from a variety of sources.

Assessment: Sequencing
Exit drawing

Differentiation: Support
Sequencing cards
Visual support
Extension
Students write a sentence describing the life cycle.
Example:
“A seed grows into a plant that makes more seeds.”', '[]'::jsonb, '{}'::uuid[], 6)
