insert into master_core_lesson_events
  (id, unit_id, subject_id, week_number, day_of_week, title, directions, learning_objectives, notes, resources, standards, display_order_within_day)
  values ('31152190-d24e-558f-9c73-99967a7adc82', '9ff375f9-74ea-5870-a272-f4e92ccfef7a', '00000000-0000-0000-0000-0000000005d7', 24, 'wed'::weekday, 'Animal Life Cycles', 'Animal Life Cycles
Vocabulary
Life cycle, Metamorphosis, Adult, Offspring

Ask:
“Do animals stay the same as they grow?”
Show baby animal pictures.

Can access this learning through the story of The Very Hungry Caterpillar

2. Direct Instruction
Introduce butterfly life cycle:
Egg
Caterpillar
Chrysalis
Butterfly
Explain metamorphosis = major change during growth.

3. Video
Short butterfly life cycle video.
Students watch for stages.

4. Guided Activity – Life Cycle Wheel
Students look at a butterfly life cycle

5. Compare Discussion
Ask:
“How is a butterfly different from a human life cycle?”

6. Exit Question (2 minutes)
“What is metamorphosis?”', '[]'::jsonb, 'Std: Know the major classifications of living things.
Investigate and understand the living world around them.

Assessment: Life cycle wheel accuracy
Oral responses

Differentiation: Support
Pre-labeled stages
Visual prompts
Extension
Students compare two life cycles:
Butterfly vs human.', '[]'::jsonb, '{}'::uuid[], 6)
