insert into master_core_lesson_events
  (id, unit_id, subject_id, week_number, day_of_week, title, directions, learning_objectives, notes, resources, standards, display_order_within_day)
  values ('7072e77e-3f09-5ab3-b277-5c281f7ac157', 'd35d79bf-6c35-5d29-b7ea-3d67b1b9ff0e', '00000000-0000-0000-0000-0000000005d7', 27, 'tue'::weekday, 'Introduce the day''s activity (5mins) - exploring facts related to the Sun…', 'Introduce the day''s activity (5mins) -  exploring facts related to the Sun, Moon, and Earth. Explain that they will be working in groups to decide which facts they think are true, false, or uncertain.
Group Activity (20 minutes)
Divide into Groups: Split the class into small groups of 3-4 students. Provide each group with a set of fact cards.
Categorizing Facts:
Instruct each group to sort their fact cards into three categories:
True: Facts they know are correct
False: Facts they believe are incorrect.
Uncertain: Facts they are unsure about.
Group Discussion:
Encourage groups to discuss and justify their reasoning for each category.
Ask questions to prompt deeper thinking, such as: "How do you know this fact is true?" or "What evidence do you have?"
Reflection (& Assessment) (5 minutes)
Discuss any surprises or new learnings that came up during the activity.
Conclusion and Next Steps (5 minutes)
Summarize Key Points: Recap what was learned about the Sun, Moon, and Earth.
Revisit List: Explain that the lists will be used throughout the unit to track learning and questions.', '[]'::jsonb, 'Std: To decide which facts they think are true, false, or uncertain about the Sun, Moon and Earth.

Assessment: Observe and note student participation and reasoning during group discussions.
Review the class lists to assess understanding and misconceptions.

Differentiation: Support: Provide additional guidance and examples to students who may need help categorizing facts. Pair them with peers who have stronger understanding for peer support.
Challenge: Encourage advanced students to research and present additional facts or evidence for the facts they categorized.', '[]'::jsonb, '{}'::uuid[], 6)
