insert into master_core_lesson_events
  (id, unit_id, subject_id, week_number, day_of_week, title, directions, learning_objectives, notes, resources, standards, display_order_within_day)
  values ('a17f20fd-ce48-51d5-bd15-e9d90ef1f197', 'd35d79bf-6c35-5d29-b7ea-3d67b1b9ff0e', '00000000-0000-0000-0000-0000000005d7', 28, 'tue'::weekday, '🌍 SESSION 3: Day, Night & Seasons', '🌍 SESSION 3: Day, Night & Seasons

🟡 1. Quick Starter – What’s Happening to the Sun? (5 mins)
🧪 Intro Activity: Spin the Earth! (10 mins)
Use a globe and flashlight to show:
Day and night (spin the globe).

Marker on home country: Watch it go from light to dark.

📊 Main Activity: Sunrise & Sunset Investigation (25 mins)
Materials:
Sunrise/sunset data for June & December (home and other countries)
Graph paper or digital chart tool
Globe/map
Instructions:
Give each group data for different countries.
Plot longest and shortest days on a bar chart or line graph.
Locate countries on a globe – What do you notice?
Discussion prompts:
Are all places bright or dark at the same time?
Why do some places have longer summers or darker winters?
Extension task:
Research “Midnight Sun” and “Polar Night” (e.g., in Norway or Antarctica) and create a poster about life there!

🧠 Reflection (10 mins)
Ask:
What causes day and night?
What causes seasons?
What happens when the Earth spins? Tilts?', '["To understand how Earth’s movement causes day/night and seasons."]'::jsonb, 'Note: نشيدة الكواكب الشمسية 🌍🔥☀️راح تحفظها اذا سمعتها😉 The Planet Song - 8 Planets of the Solar System Song for Kids | KidsLearningTube The Planets Song - The Kiboomers Preschool Songs & Nursery Rhymes About The Solar System

Assessment: Practical Demonstration: Observe participation in the globe/torch activity—do they understand how day/night works?Comparison and Reasoning: Can you explain seasonal differences between countries?

Differentiation: Support:
Provide pre-labeled diagrams or sentence starters for children to explain day/night.
Use a simplified globe with only key countries marked.

Challenge:
Ask advanced students to research the "midnight sun" or polar night and explain why they happen.
Let them explore how Earth''s tilt affects shadow length throughout the year.', '[]'::jsonb, '{}'::uuid[], 6)
