  values ('f4e87a6d-57bd-57f8-857c-fc5f745cd20b', '28e56d40-c191-52c4-8b1e-be172fdb38f5', '00000000-0000-0000-0000-0000000005d2', 29, 'wed'::weekday, 'Guided Reading:/Grammar', 'Guided Reading:/Grammar:

 Quick Review of Character Traits-

Rotations:
https://drive.google.com/file/d/1y38EBQQ39vV40XdbvC95RJh9dj000qdM/view?usp=drive_link

Rotations: (12-15 min each)

Group 1- RIT Score Pack with teacher
Group 2- Independent Reading
Group 3- Task Cards
Group 4- IXL/SeeSaw

IXL:
G3- Character Traits
G4- Character Traits
G5- Character Traits
G1-Character Dialogue for Traits

SeeSaw:
Character and Settings Review
Alexander Who’s Not Going to Move
Chrysanthemum
FAST Model', '[]'::jsonb, 'Std: Reading LiteratureRL.5.5 – Text Structure
CCSS RL.5.5: Explain how a series of chapters, scenes, or stanzas fits together to provide the overall structure of a particular story, drama, or poem.
EE.RL.5.2 – Theme / Summary
EE.RL.5.2: Determine a theme of a story, drama, or poem; recount the text, including characters in a story or drama, or details from a poem.
Writing
W.5.3a – Narrative Writing
CCSS W.5.3a: Orient the reader by establishing a situation and introducing a narrator and/or characters; organize an event sequence that unfolds naturally.
Reading Informational
EE.RI.5.1 – Refer to Details
EE.RI.5.1: Identify details in an informational text to support what the text says explicitly.
Language / Conventions
L.5.2.E – Spelling
CCSS L.5.2.e: Spell grade-appropriate words correctly, consulting references as needed.
EE.L.5.2.H – Conventions
EE.L.5.2.H: Use learned spelling patterns and generalize to spell new words.
L.5.2 – Conventions of Standard English
CCSS L.5.2: Demonstrate command of the conventions of standard English capitalization, punctuation, and spelling when writing.
L.5.4 – Vocabulary Acquisition
CCSS L.5.4: Determine or clarify the meaning of unknown and multiple-meaning words and phrases based on grade 5 reading and content.
EE.L.5.2 – Writing Conventions
EE.L.5.2: Demonstrate understanding of conventions of standard English.
EE.L.5.4 – Vocabulary Meaning
EE.L.5.4: Determine the meaning of words and phrases in context.

Assessment: Writing-

Reading- Informal Assessment of questions asked and completed during guided reading.
Grammar-The ability to complete IXL and SeeSaw successfully

Differentiation: Writing-

Reading- Provide a graphic organizer for struggling readers.

Grammar- Create character trait webs.', '[]'::jsonb, '{}'::uuid[], 1)
