insert into master_core_lesson_events
  (id, unit_id, subject_id, week_number, day_of_week, title, directions, learning_objectives, notes, resources, standards, display_order_within_day)
  values ('02eeb8b1-bb3f-5e53-8c81-ee26d67e8b96', '28e56d40-c191-52c4-8b1e-be172fdb38f5', '00000000-0000-0000-0000-0000000005d2', 30, 'tue'::weekday, 'Guided Reading:/Grammar', 'Guided Reading:/Grammar:
Figurative Language Posters
Similes & Metaphors
🔹 Warm-up (3 min): "Finish the Sentence" Game
Write "As fast as a __" and "He was a __ in the race" on the board or orally.
Whole Group Activity- Call on students to come up and select the correct metaphor/simile. https://www.twinkl.com/go/resource/complete-the-metaphor-or-simile-interactive-matching-activity-au-l-1661237937
🔹 Lesson (10 min): I Do: Watch Video (group activity).
 You Do: Students complete the activity.
IXL:
G4- Similes/Metaphors
G5- Similes/Metaphors
G4-Identify Similes/Metaphors
G5- Identify Similes/Metaphors

SeeSaw:
Simile/|Metaphor Sort
 Simile/Metaphor Practice

Kahoot:
https://create.kahoot.it/details/4258d005-c591-49c9-af39-709d2aa3fe78

Rotations: (12-15 min each)

Group 1- RIT Score Pack with teacher
Group 2- Independent Reading
Group 3- Task Cards
Group 4- IXL/SeeSaw', '[]'::jsonb, 'Std: Reading Literature (RL)
RL.5.4 – Determine the meaning of words and phrases as they are used in a text, including figurative language such as metaphors and similes. RL.5.9 – Compare and contrast stories in the same genre on their approaches to similar themes and topics.
