  values ('8324b4a7-87d6-54fc-9b38-66ef332a52f8', 'd35d79bf-6c35-5d29-b7ea-3d67b1b9ff0e', '00000000-0000-0000-0000-0000000005d7', 30, 'wed'::weekday, 'Recap on ideas covered from previous week and consolidate on seasons -', 'Recap on ideas covered from previous week and consolidate on seasons -
Watch: Earth''s Tilt 1: The Reason for the Seasons

Finish off elements of session 2 from previous week that may not have been completed due to other things happening alongside preparing for MAP testing:

 Day, Night & Seasons

📊 Main Activity: Sunrise & Sunset Investigation (25 mins)
Materials:
Sunrise/sunset data for June & December (home and other countries)
Graph paper or digital chart tool
Globe/map
Instructions:
Give data for different countries.
Plot longest and shortest days on a bar chart or line graph.
Locate countries on a globe – What do you notice?
Discussion prompts:
Are all places bright or dark at the same time?
Why do some places have longer summers or darker winters?
Extension task:
Research “Midnight Sun” and “Polar Night” (e.g., in Norway or Antarctica) and create a poster about life there!

🧠 Reflection (10 mins)
Ask:
What causes day and night?
What causes seasons?
What happens when the Earth spins? Tilts?
The results show longer days in June for the Northern Hemisphere locations (Doha, London, NYC, Tokyo) and shorter days in December. The opposite is true for Sydney in the Southern Hemisphere. This variation is expected due to the Earth''s tilt.', '["To understand how Earth’s movement causes day/night and seasons."]'::jsonb, 'Note: Qatar (Doha) June 1st, 2024: Sunrise: 04:43, Sunset: 18:21 = Daylight Duration: 13 hours 38 minutes June 15th, 2024: Sunrise: 04:43, Sunset: 18:25 = Daylight Duration: 13 hours 42 minutes June 30th, 2024: Sunrise: 04:47, Sunset: 18:29 = Daylight Duration: 13 hours 42 minutes December 1st, 2024: Sunrise: 06:03, Sunset: 16:42 = Daylight Duration: 10 hours 39 minutes December 15th, 2024: Sunrise: 06:12, Sunset: 16:45 = Daylight Duration: 10 hours 33 minutes December 31st, 2024: Sunrise: 06:20, Sunset: 16:54 = Daylight Duration: 10 hours 34 minutes United Kingdom (London) June 1st, 2024: Sunrise: ~04:52, Sunset: ~21:08 = Daylight Duration: ~16 hours 16 minutes June 15th, 2024: Sunrise: ~04:43, Sunset: ~21:20 = Daylight Duration: ~16 hours 37 minutes June 30th, 2024: Sunrise: ~04:53, Sunset: ~21:18 = Daylight Duration: ~16 hours 25 minutes December 1st, 2024: Sunrise: ~07:44, Sunset: ~15:56 = Daylight Duration: ~8 hours 12 minutes December 15th, 2024: Sunrise: ~08:02, Sunset: ~15:53 = Daylight Duration: ~7 hours 51 minutes December 31st, 2024: Sunrise: ~08:08, Sunset: ~16:05 = Daylight Duration: ~7 hours 57 minutes United States (New York City) June 1st, 2024: Sunrise: ~05:26, Sunset: ~20:24 = Daylight Duration: ~14 hours 58 minutes June 15th, 2024: Sunrise: ~05:23, Sunset: ~20:32 = Daylight Duration: ~15 hours 9 minutes June 30th, 2024: Sunrise: ~05:31, Sunset: ~20:32 = Daylight Duration: ~15 hours 1 minute December 1st, 2024: Sunrise: ~07:04, Sunset: ~16:32 = Daylight Duration: ~9 hours 28 minutes December 15th, 2024: Sunrise: ~07:17, Sunset: ~16:29 = Daylight Duration: ~9 hours 12 minutes December 31st, 2024: Sunrise: ~07:20, Sunset: ~16:39 