Description: Building on their character work, students will dive into the importance of setting in fiction. With guidance from the "Brainstorming Settings" worksheet, they will brainstorm and select where and when their stories will take place. Students will describe the places, times, and environments that will shape their stories, using sensory details to make their settings vivid. By the end of class, students will have a character and a setting, forming the foundation for their stories.', '[]'::jsonb, '', '[]'::jsonb, '{}'::uuid[], 2)
