Description: Today, students will focus on the heart of any good story: the problem or challenge the main character faces. Using the "Planning Out the Problem" and "Goals and Challenges" sheets, students will determine what their character wants and what obstacles stand in the way. The class will discuss how problems drive stories forward and brainstorm possible solutions. Students will then begin laying out the basic structure of their story, using the "Fiction Story Plan" to organize their ideas.', '[]'::jsonb, '', '[]'::jsonb, '{}'::uuid[], 2)
