insert into master_core_lesson_events
  (id, unit_id, subject_id, week_number, day_of_week, title, directions, learning_objectives, notes, resources, standards, display_order_within_day)
  values ('45e6cb18-fa05-5b71-a463-5ab3642d692b', 'd35d79bf-6c35-5d29-b7ea-3d67b1b9ff0e', '00000000-0000-0000-0000-0000000005d7', 34, 'mon'::weekday, 'Key Vocabulary', 'Key Vocabulary
Rain, Soil, Plants, Water, Grow, Earth systems, Interact

What Helps Plants Grow? (5 minutes)
Show a plant, cup of soil, and spray bottle.
Ask:
“What does a plant need to grow?”
“Where does water come from?”
“What does soil do?”
Record responses
Explicit Teaching (10 minutes)
Assessment question picture.
Explain:
Rain gives water.
Soil holds water and nutrients.
Plants absorb water and nutrients from the soil.
Plants grow because rain and soil help them.

Teacher model:
“Rain gives water to the soil. The soil helps the plants grow.”
Create an anchor chart:

Build the Sentence (10 minutes)
Students repeat and complete sentence frames:
Rain gives __________.
Soil helps __________.
Plants use __________ to grow.
 Exit Ticket (5 minutes)
Oral response or written:
“How do rain, soil, and plants work together?”', '["Explain how rain, soil, and plants work together.", "Success Criteria", "I can name the parts in the picture (rain, soil, plants).", "I can explain how they help each other.", "I can write one complete sentence about how they interact."]'::jsonb, 'Note: No Exhibition this year

Std: Understand that Earth is made of different systems (water, land, air, and living things).
Describe how Earth’s systems work together to support life.
Gather evidence from pictures and observations.

Assessment Opportunities
Level of participation in discussion
Completed drawing and sentence
Exit response

Differentiation: Support
Vocabulary bank with visual aids
Incomplete sentence prompts:
“Rain provides __________.”
“The soil helps __________.”
Challenge & Extension
Compose a pair of sentences detailing the connection between three systems - of rain, soil and plant.', '[]'::jsonb, '{}'::uuid[], 6)
