  values ('8589bb42-0311-50f3-946d-9738a8f7a1aa', 'd35d79bf-6c35-5d29-b7ea-3d67b1b9ff0e', '00000000-0000-0000-0000-0000000005d7', 34, 'wed'::weekday, 'Key Vocabulary', 'Key Vocabulary
Recycle, Reduce, Reuse, Save water, Plant trees, Protect, Resources, Community
Sorting Good Choices (5 minutes)
Show pictures.
Students sort into:
Helps the Earth
Hurts the Earth
Explicit Teaching (10 minutes)
Discuss ways communities can protect resources:
Recycle paper and plastic
Save water
Plant trees
Pick up litter
Reuse materials
Create anchor chart.
Guided Practice (10 minutes)
Complete sentence frames:
Communities can __________.
We protect water by __________.
People can plant __________.

Independent Writing (10 minutes)
Students write two sentences.
Example:
Communities can recycle and save water. People can plant trees and clean parks.
 Exit Ticket (5 minutes)
Students share one action they can take at home.', '["Identify actions communities can take to protect Earth’s resources.", "Success Criteria", "I can name ways to help the Earth.", "I can explain how communities protect resources.", "I can write two complete sentences."]'::jsonb, 'Note: No Exhibition this year

Std: Recognize ways people conserve natural resources.
Describe actions that help protect Earth.
Communicate ideas in complete sentences.

Assessment Opportunities
Picture sorting
Completed writing
Exit sharing

Differentiation: Support
Word bank with pictures
Sentence starters
Extension
Students explain why these actions are important.', '[]'::jsonb, '{}'::uuid[], 6)
